A moment in history that would cause a ripple in the vast ocean of world history which would change so much, yet so few know the true cause and effect that would result from this David and Goliath story.  Countries were born in the back of this fight.  Louisiana Purchase, largest real estate deal ever, only happened because of that fight. No way to be singing “from sea to shining sea” without that.  You’re welcome America.  If you haven’t heard of the Battle of Vertières, go check it out. 
#haiti #vertieres #freedom #history

Beach please.
There is absolutely nothing better then a little vitamin sea.  No matter you are going through, a quick dip will for sure make you feel better.  Well it does for me anyways.  Add in good company and a few cocktails and you have yourself a recipe for a great day.  Really missing a classic Sunday funday today.
#haiti #islandlife #sonyalpha #wanderlust #paradise

What’s a trip to the Exumas without a stop at @theswimmingpigs .  I thought it was going to be a bunch of small pigs but this was some huge sea salt marinated griot.  It was so cool to see all the pigs swim out to the boat as soon as we got there.  They kept on trying to bite the @gopro which was quite amusing.  Can’t wait to take my kids, they would love it.  Everyone have an awesome weekend.
#swimmingpigsbahamas #gopro #itsbetterinthebahamas #islandlife #wanderlust

After 36 hours of non stop going, only stupid for fuel, we finally made it to the Exumas.  This has been one of the places that has always been very high up on my list of places I wanted to go and it didn’t disappoint.  I always wanted to be on the boat that I saw going through there from a plane and maybe someone saw me and thought the same thing.  The only problem is now that know what it is was like, I no longer want to go back, I need to go back 😝.
#droneoftheday #itsbetterinthebahamas #wanderlust #islandlife #dronestagram

There’s just something special about sunsets.  The shift between day and night, the beauty between something ending and beginning.  On a side note, if you have never been to inagua at sunset, the mosquitoes are actually the size of small airplanes.  Felt like I was in Top Gun.  After that attack, we just decided to go straight through the night for 15 hours to our next stop.  We had a completely clear night and the night sky 🌌 put on quite the show.  Smooth ride all the way to the Exumas.
#sunsetphotography #sonyalpha #islandlife #wanderlust #itsbetterinthebahamas

Just weeks ago I had the chance to do something I’ve always wanted to do, cross the Bahamas on a boat.  There is a omething humbling about being in the middle of the ocean with no land in sight at the pure mercy of the ocean.  Luckily, the seas were absolutely beautiful for our first couple of days, never getting more than 2 foot seas.  First stop was Great Inagua, where Morton’s salt has the second largest salt producing operation in North America.  Little known fact, King Christophe built a summer retreat at the Northeast point of Inagua, it is believed that he also has a cache of gold buried there.  Might have to go back with a shovel.
Great Inagua, Bahamas
